article.description: — Malik Miller’s 27 points helped Morgan State defeat Penn State-Greater Allegheny 130-49 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Morgan St. gets 130-49 win over Penn St.-Greater Allegheny
article.linkText: Morgan St. gets 130-49 win over Penn St.-Greater Allegheny
article.story: BALTIMORE -- — Malik Miller’s 27 points helped Morgan State defeat Penn State-Greater Allegheny 130-49 on Thursday night. Miller also contributed 11 rebounds, eight assists, and five steals for the Bears (1-1). Will Thomas added 25 points while shooting 10 of 15 from the field and 4 for 4 from the line, and they also had three steals. David McCullough went 7 of 8 from the field to finish with 18 points, while adding three steals. Bryce Phillips finished with 12 points and two steals. Christopher Killings added 12 points for Penn State-Greater Allegheny. Damon Gamble also recorded six points. NEXT UP Morgan State visits VCU in its next matchup on Saturday. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
